(64, 1, '2023-12-23 10:36:15', '2023-12-23 03:36:15', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Ten white swallows returned home </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The Tathagata often rests on the hem of his spring robe </p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Shoulders tilted to the stream of silk</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A pair of peach mounds blooming on the fragrant snow</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Vehicles on the road dust flower shop<br>Through the white mist, the streets are fading in autumn<br>The sound of birds is soaked in two seasons<br>The falling seeds become colder and more indifferent as the clouds pass by</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The cricket was sad and fell asleep<br>The faint sound of ivory and mist flying<br>When people return, stars bloom in their hands<br>With shoes drenched in moonlight, the heels are long and dreamy</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I advise it to sing on the shore<br>I changed my shirt and indifferently raised my head<br>I thought there was someone upstairs<br>On spring day, gently sow damask balls</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Long hair ends in the clouds far away<br>Yellow butterfly pistil and evil emblem fly<br>Use your arms to hold your hands<br>Exchange silk scarves to remember sad days</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>From ancient mountain birds</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Coming here, I left apricot seeds at the end of the forest</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>From you close green comedy</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Returning through desire, his soul blossomed into a flower of sadness</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Yes, I\'m afraid of the rain</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Also took him to the downstream bridge</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This river flows in just one stream</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The clouds at the beginning of the river darken human hair at the end of the river</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In the past, I was pregnant with my husband</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In spring I wear a peach shirt</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Autumn in blue sky</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In winter, I changed my floral shirt again</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>On the way back to pick mustard buds</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Just bring along a field of eggplants</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Well, you don\'t love me</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Climbing up the grapefruit branch, I miss you with tears in my eyes</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Why do you take small, hesitant steps?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>By the bridge, the dew fell a few plums</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>At night, light candles and write poetry</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The sound of footsteps still echoes half of my poem</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The white lovebirds have flown away</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The sound is heard earnestly in the early winter sky</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>At midnight, I covered myself with a pink blanket</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Listen to the cold flowers in the fields again</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The bird died under the flower tree</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The cry fell in the middle of the pale river</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Tomorrow he will die under the peach tree</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Crying, I would like to shed my tears into eternity</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Old city wall, old stele</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The soul of the sea mulberry calls in the flying reed flag</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In the afternoon, the jade bracelet was exchanged hands</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Give each other silk scarves at the end of the day to prepare</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The long night is full of flower pistils<br>Birds chirping at the tomb door and the moonlight knocks on the stele<br>Please invite your hair back<br>Looking at the moon, I couldn\'t help but let the oath fly away</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>White flowers fall on the side of the road<br>Fragrant petals convey the message of impermanence, snow and ice<br>The little bee just emerged from the net<br>Also tilting the golden stamens of the wings fell off</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In the spring, I put it in the stream to play</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Listen to the birds singing in the mountains calling for flowers from the sky</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Scoop the bottle of cool water over</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Visit a certain village to ask for old tea</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Birds abandoned the sparse flower cave</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>People from blue hair to both summer and east</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Go to the mountains to look for dodder seeds</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Suddenly, I saw a pair of cranes flying</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>People return to the western misty mountain peak</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I lay alone and wait for the day when the luffa flowers bloom</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The south wharf has Giang Ha street</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Tilting the jade slope, the slope is evil and intoxicating</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>By chance I met her here</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The difference between the heels of the moon and the thin figure of the willow tree</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Crossing the river, someone suddenly felt sad</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Looking at the yellow flowers falling on the road in early autumn</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I will never remember tomorrow</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The mulberry field still remembers the grave even if it is empty</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Any bird\'s feet perch on the dune</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When the horse is down, some people are sad to hide the bird</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Waiting for you to dream all night long</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The Ngan River becomes longer and blurry</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>He lay down on the grass pillow and waited for flowers</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>My shirt is a white crane and I\'m a Thai spoiled girl</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I started washing my face and feet like that</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Leaning over the water beads invites the void to return</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Gathering incense and worshiping Bodhi</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The lipstick sinks into the seeds of samsara</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I\'ll come back and shake off my clothes<br>Moon pillow to wake up next to the hyacinth hill<br>That once upon a time there was a man who resigned from a mandarin<br>Go to the mountains to find a cave with golden flowers sleeping soundly</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Moon scarves from hand to hand<br>Half melted from stream sand, half ground into dew<br>Tomorrow my heart feels sad<br>The piece of moon manifests the paradise of play</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Spiders clinging to the sky\'s web</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Birds pass by to inquire about the dead person\'s grave</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Dropping plum seeds on the side of the road</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Next spring, it grows between the foot of a flower tree</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Yellow buds bloom in March</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Waking up in the middle of the night to look at the evil moon</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Not like the willow tree on the poplar shore</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Green hair amidst impermanence and emptiness</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Tomorrow is fragrant in autumn and winter</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The comb I combed lost a couple of green threads</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Pair of pink canaries on a branch</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Bewildered, I forgot to preen my hair and apply makeup</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Spring wears leaves on thousands of trees</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Autumn wears a romantic yellow butterfly</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Nam Hoa Cave has a Zen master</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Exchange the scriptures for wine, your mind will overflow</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Late at night the candle flame glows yellow<br>The scriptures are dotted with rows of terns<br>Which idea turns into a thousand flowers?<br>Which word engraves the moon on the hem of the nun\'s robe?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Cooing the stream in a whisper<br>The dream of the three worlds is nothing but a flower<br>Nuns appear among us<br>Ruby buds lift up the moon dress</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The sound of birds in infinity</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Blooming profusely in the cinnamon forest</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The sound of you singing in the middle of the church</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>God returns in shocking scriptures</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Who can remember all the yellow flowers?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Who can drink all the dew and moonlight?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Guess who will dry out the veins of sorrow?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Then I will put my hair on the bridge to welcome someone</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I came back with dew on my shoulders</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Footprints are long orchids blooming at night</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>From you revealed a magical smile</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Autumn disappears in the field of grass and flowers</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Worn clogs mixed with the sound of larks</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The monk crossed this bridge with a bamboo stick</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Looking at the banks of the cold stream, flowers fly</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I feel sorry for the way the water flows forever</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There is a blue marlin</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Swim to the source and bathe in the spring stream</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Halfway through the fish line, the fish met the rainbow</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Ask why the clouds left the gods to play</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Even though tomorrow\'s tent is grassy on the horizon</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Burning the incense of the old furnace makes people cry in poetry</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I still have pink cheeks</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The old hair is still foggy now</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Go to the mountains and pick this flower<br>Looking at the bottom of the stream, the shadow is faint<br>I always look like I\'m not sure if it\'s me<br>After bathing, put on your clothes and sing songs back to the village</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Hands wearing jade bracelets<br>Your shirt flutters with golden silk<br>I\'m tired of looking for you<br>Stop here and ask: what is ignorance?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Ask the cauldron that lands on the banks of the canal</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Why bother with the picture not being damaged?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Vac said: Dear Thien Thu</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Why wear the flimsy Zen monk\'s robe?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Water has been moving since time immemorial</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>People standing on the bank looking downstream</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Somewhere under the wharf there are fresh flowers</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Tying the old boat, there were people looking at the river</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Since the day I left for my husband</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I kept the white shirt and the pink shirt I brought</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This afternoon I was shocked again</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Ten years of old clothes turning yellow and tears turning green</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A pair of small birds on a branch</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Urging each other to weave green grass nests on the side of the road</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Half a lifetime of wandering clouds and water</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The Zen master cut grass and offered it to the Buddha</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The afternoon mound was filled with mist and dust</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>If you ask, you will know where the golden branches rest</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Next to the fox\'s grave, the fox burrows</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Birds chirping as loudly as her humming</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>At the end of spring we looked again</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The young lady stood on the grave of the withered wildflowers</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Early in the fall we took a ferry over</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>On the side of the road, the grave grass is yellow with chrysanthemums and flowers</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Bamboo leaves the wind indifferently</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I leaned against the door thinking I wasn\'t married yet</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>River, please be green</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>In the spring, take a basket to the fields to pick up flowers</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The long road is filled with singing birds<br>People still wear hats to follow the sunset<br>The chess game displays white peach blossoms<br>Why go up the mountain to darken the moon in an empty cup?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Autumn hills squeeze streams of pink clouds<br>Blue birds scattered across the stream of fairy flowers<br>The wick of sadness and fire is waiting for you<br>Who poured this oil out of ancient tears?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Welcoming you is like waiting for a bird in the sky</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The spring beach is parked in the early morning and the autumn smoke is removed in the afternoon</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I still have the old white shirt</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>There will always be tears in you</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Smell fragrant incense and chant sage sutras</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Spring blood is cold in the bones and skin</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The temple garden has ca buds</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Late night mist: dharma protection of evil moon: no door</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Fresh apricot wings bloom next to the dunes</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The rain is speckled with bright white incense branches</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Autumn and winter are hidden in the sky</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The seeds fall and the pearls fall apart and the flowers fall apart</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The village gate opens with stars<br>Nha Lan faintly hears the sound of chickens in the neighborhood<br>Go to the temple and offer a plate of jasmine flowers<br>Suddenly the cold moon shone on the Patriarch\'s body</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The afternoon bell rings in quiet contemplation<br>The sound is filled with floating heavenly script seeds<br>Tune returns to his hand and hides a bunch of flowers<br>The Buddha\'s earthen heel blooms with everlasting roses</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The moon\'s shadow covers the porch</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The pile of pipa seeds sprouts mixed with incense</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Autumn wind from far away</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Returning to the wooden hole on the side of the road, there was silence</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>My shirt\'s hem is thousands of sims</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Half eagerly calling, half waiting silently</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Since when have we loved each other?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Seeing this, I pretended to be indifferent and the smoke flew away</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>It\'s like a mountain meeting a cloud</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Like dew, the petals are thin and dull</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>When I woke up, I was still sleeping</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The story that happened ten years ago is heartbreaking again</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Lotus branches and leaves hold clear dew</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The gray shirt with the sky is not sad</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Which hand tilts the poet\'s hat?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Which hand holds the pale Bodhi rosary?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The eyebrows are high phoenixes</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Ripe lips with plump peach corners</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Her voice broke into poetry</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Chant the wisdom sutra on the sheet of smoke and clouds</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Your hair smells of the forest<br>My arms are long and have ivory-shaped flower buds<br>Blue eyes of amitabha vow<br>Light steps of incense mixed with sunset birds</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Her eyes lull the soft cradle<br>Lull my soul to sleep for a thousand wonderful nights<br>You are a flower that represents a person<br>I am a butterfly that returns to the sky</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>One night sleeping in the clouds</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I remember in my past life there was a heavenly incense tree</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The white grapefruit tree smells of life</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Bud is Buddha\'s hand pointing to people crossing the river</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The green trees are dressed in pink mist</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The snow bird in the field flew away</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The cold cry chilled my palms</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The finger suddenly let go and filled the heart with flowers</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I\'m at the door polishing my ivory hands</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Winter orchid roots bloom through several branches</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The day I marinated my blue shirt</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The lovebird earnestly hangs on the branch calling for autumn</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The nun went home and closed the temple door to practice</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Early tomorrow, open the gate to sweep the rose garden</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Autumn crowns the double-flowered broom</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Occasionally offering strange incense and butterflies encircling their wings</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The monk reached the top of the meditation forest<br>In my heart, a halo of sunset suddenly lit up<br>Fingers blooming with fragrant peach buds<br>Hold the pure land in a wonderful direction</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Guests from far away remember each other<br>Go up the hill and pick up a basket of myrtle as a gift<br>Collect spring water to make a tea pot<br>Picking gourds to cook a bowl of flower soup and laughing hoarsely</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Enter the mountain cave and enter nirvana</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The star blooms a golden flower at the slit door</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Tomorrow, no donors will listen</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Look up and ask for a raft of blue clouds</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I have yellow flowers waiting for you<br>My body appears to sing on the branch of the apricot tree<br>The world welcomes this dreamland<br>The Ngan River finds a place beyond its fate</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Take me to find the golden flower cave', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '63-revision-v1', '', '', '2023-12-23 10:36:15', '2023-12-23 03:36:15', '', 63, 'http://localhost:8080/tinhay4/?p=64', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
