(70, 1, '2023-12-23 14:54:00', '2023-12-23 07:54:00', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>This is a really strange poem. There are up to 8 different readings<br>I love the bright spring scene<br>The pleasures of poetry are filled with wine and cups<br>Flowers placed on bamboo hedges with blue branches<br>The leaves are fragrant with fresh spring fragrance<br>Passengers go back and forth waiting for the river to calm down<br>Back and forth the boat waits for a crowded dock<br>The distant sound of singing and singing is deep<br>A gentle silhouette with smiling eyes. 2. Read the original lesson backwards from the bottom up (we get lesson 2)<br>Smiling and smiling with graceful eyes<br>The bass and bass guitar sing in the distance<br>People crowded the docks waiting for the boat to go back and forth<br>The river\'s waves are calm, waiting for guests to pass by<br>Fresh spring color and scent mixed with leaves<br>Green bamboo branches hung with flowers on the hedge<br>Filled with a cup of poetic wine and joy<br>Bright spring light loves us.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Remove the first two words of each sentence in the original lesson (we get lesson 3) (five words and eight sentences, equal rhyme rule)<br>Bright spring scene<br>Poetry and wine cups are full<br>Bamboo hedge with green branches<br>The fresh scent of spring<br>Guests wait for the river to calm down<br>The boat waiting at the dock was crowded with people<br>The sound of singing is low<br>A shadow with smiling eyes.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Remove the last two words of each sentence in the original lesson, read backwards from the bottom up (we get lesson 4)<br>(five words, eight sentences, rules in equal rhyme)<br>Whose eyes are glossy and graceful<br>The instrument sings in the distance<br>The dock waits for the boat to go back and forth<br>The river waits for visitors to cross again<br>The colors of spring blend with the leaves<br>Bamboo branches hang flowers on the hedge<br>A cup of wine and poetic joy<br>The spring light loves me.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>3. Remove the last three words of each sentence in the original lesson (we get lesson 5) (eight sentences &amp; four words)<br>I love spring scenery<br>The joy of wine poetry<br>Flowers installed on bamboo hedges<br>The leaves blend with the scent of spring<br>Back and forth, customers wait<br>Back and forth the boat waits<br>Far away the sound of singing<br>Let go of someone\'s shadow.<br>4. Remove the first three words of each sentence in the original lesson, read backwards from the bottom up (we get lesson 6) (eight sentences &amp; four words)<br>Smile and smile at someone\'s eyes<br>Play bass and sing<br>Crowds of people waiting<br>The calm waves of the river wait<br>Fresh spring color<br>Green bamboo branches<br>Fill a cup of wine<br>Bright spring light.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Remove the first four words of each sentence in the original lesson (we get lesson 7) (eight sentences &amp; three words)<br>Bright light<br>The cup is full and empty<br>Blue branches<br>Bright colors<br>The river is calm<br>The wharf is crowded<br>Bass guitar<br>Smiling eyes.<br>5. Remove the last four words of each sentence in the original lesson, read backwards from the bottom up (we get lesson 8) (eight sentences &amp; three words)<br>Sleek silhouette<br>Distant hum<br>The boat goes back and forth<br>Guests come over again<br>Fragrance mixed with leaves<br>Hedge with flowers<br>Poetry is fun<br>Canh loves me</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'The poem has 8 ways to read', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'the-poem-has-8-ways-to-read', '', '', '2023-12-24 09:23:43', '2023-12-24 02:23:43', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8080/tinhay4/?p=70', 0, 'post', '', 0),
