 foreign invasion, Vietnamese society was completely turned upside down, which, directly related to the fate of our grandfather, was the decline of Confucianism.That decline leads to the loss of a whole class of people who, at one time, we still considered symbols of traditional Vietnamese culture. “There\'s nothing wrong with the word grapes. \"I\'m tired, even I\'m lying down,\" Tu Xuong once cried out, aching and heartbroken. In that chaotic situation, students flocked to learn Western language. He had to say goodbye to the school, the holy words, the literary reviews and reading sessions to accept the sad way of making a living by writing couplets for Tet every spring.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Luckily for him, the change in cultural traditions is often slower than the change in history, politics, society, and the educational and examination systems. The masses still have the habit of respecting Chinese characters, at least during Tet days. That gave him, on the one hand, a way to make a living, and on the other hand, he still had friends who knew how to appreciate his talent, even if they were friends passing by. That enthusiastic enjoyment made his ironic seat on the sidewalk feel warm.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>The first two stanzas, therefore, not only speak of the resonance and harmony between humans and nature but also of the interconnection between humans. The monk did not sit alone with the peach blossoms. Besides him, there are also loyal customers. Around them, spring is fragrant and colorful. Pretty. And fun. Joy overflows into the storyteller\'s words: his voice is loud and strong with words starting with the crisp consonant \"d\" (peach, do, red, east…); He spoke quickly, told in one go, without stopping, very enthusiastic, full of passion, very excited: in two verses, each of four lines, in terms of grammar, in fact, it was just one sentence, one just sentence:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Every year when the peach blossoms bloom, I see an old man displaying red ink and paper on a crowded street.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Many people wrote notes praising his talent: \"The palm flowers have features like a phoenix dancing and a dragon flying.\"</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'Mr. Do\'s poem', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '73-revision-v1', '', '', '2023-12-23 15:01:41', '2023-12-23 08:01:41', '', 73, 'http://localhost:8080/tinhay4/?p=74', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(75, 1, '2023-12-23 15:05:22', '2023-12-23 08:05:22', '<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>An old man turned to me and asked: \"How many friends do you have?\". \"Why do you ask that? I have 10 or 20 friends, but I can only remember a few of their names.\"</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>He smiled as if he understood and then sadly nodded:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>She must be very lucky to have so many friends. But think about what she was saying. There are too many people she did not know the name of it! You are not just someone for her to say: hello!<br>You are the person who has a soft shoulder for her to cry on.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A well into which to pour all your risks and increase your value.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>You were a hand to pull her up from darkness and despair when everyone she called “friends” had pushed her into.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>A true friend is an ally who cannot be swayed or bribed. Be a voice to keep her name alive when others have forgotten.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>But the most necessary thing in a friend is a heart, a strong and towering wall. From the hearts of those friends we will have the most wonderful love.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>So think about what I say, every word is sincere.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>And answer me again, girl, how many friends do you have?</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I smiled at him and replied: \"At least I have a friend, old man!\"</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Thanks for being my friend!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->', 'How many friends do you have?', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'how-many-friends-do-you-have', '', '', '2023-12-24 09:20:07', '2023-12-24 02:20:07', '', 0, 'http://localhost:8080/tinhay4/?p=75', 0, 'post', '', 0),
